<br>
Bards = twisting<br>
<br>
If you don't like it, I'm sorry, but being a bard isn't you.<br>
<br>
We are unique, and that uniqueness is what makes us. Twisting is part of what it is to be a bard.<br>
<br>
And I'm not saying the removal of twisting would destroy us. We're bards, we adapt.<br>
<br>
And, I'm not saying people who don't like twisting can't be (good) bards. They can of course. And besides there are times I don't like twisting myself.<br>
<br>
The argument that twisting wasn't intended is bs: our current songs are what we're using and they were created with twisting in mind.<br>
