<br>
Devs intended to make bards a single song singing class, it was the players who used the limited duration of songs to 'twist' more than one.  Soon it just became the standard, like many things in EQ do.  Just like Feign Death was not intended to be a pulling tool, it was implimented as a means of clearing agro on Monks who pulled agro and consistantly died.<br>
<br>
I have played a Bard since August of 99, a druid before that.  I had no problems at all with my wrist until acouple of months ago.  Previous to that I considered posts on wrists problems to be 'not my problem', much as many of the posters here do.  <br>
<br>
Just like Jaos, I now also use a script for twisting, it is the only way I can keep playing.  All it does is a 3 or 4 song twist, whatever I need at the time.  I still have to manually slow, debuff, mez ect.  After actually using it, I strongly belive it is the way things should be.<br>
<br>
At this time my wrist is still not fully recovered, and for those who suggest playing another class.... I'd rather quit, the rest bore me to death. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/cjs27/twinkzignome.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tamsindyresoul>Tamsin Dyresoul</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#330000>(7/5/04 2:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19562.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed solution to the pains of twisting.</span><hr size=1> Started bard in November of '99.  From what I've always remembered, twisting was an unintended invention of players that, like many other things, became a part of the game.  Toss it in there with kiting, FD pulling, etc.  <br>
<br>
However, unlike some of the other unintended 'features', the game has been balanced around twisting since before the first Iksar crawled out of it's egg.  Well balanced?  Maybe not.  But the ability has been taken into account for a very long time.<br>
<br>
Fast forward to today.  We are in what many might consider the twilight of EQ.  Unfortunately, not every one has the knowledge or the understanding to set up their work/play areas to be ergonomically correct.  In fact, if your like me, I still do the old 11,22,33 (sometimes 44) scenario.  Moving in on 5 years of that, it's getting old, and sometimes painful.  Not since Asteroids have I hit so many buttons <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think the main question here is how many songs up at once is considered normal or balanced?  The two answers are, of course, 3 or 4.  <br>
<br>
Setting up a system that can reliably keep 3 songs going at once is fair.  Doing the same for 4 songs is a bit beyond me since, as stated on another post I have made, seeing 4 songs in your song buff box does not equal 4 songs necessarily for your group.  Or Raid.  When two-boxing with my cleric I often noticed songs dropping on my bard while being active on cleric.<br>
<br>
Now, if you want to go this route, the question becomes how to best maintain a twist without, well, twisting.  We have seen some suggestions in this thread that aren't all bad.  From an old fart's standpoint, IF you want to go that route, make it similiar to the sometimes suggested 'Song stuck in head' AA.  You get 3 songs constant.  Start song only.  Starting a 4th song kicks the 3rd song off.  Let me explain:<br>
<br>
So, what you get is a situation where you click 3 songs in succession to start your twist. Or two, or one.  Doesn't matter as long you understand you will have a maximum of 3.  Click 1 WoZ, Click 2 WoM, Click 3 PoV, Click 4 Riz pushes PoV off and you got Riz, WoZ, and WoM.  Go to a 5th song, let's say Niv's since it's popular on the boards lately, push Niv's, you got song 1 Niv's, song 2 Riz, song 3 WoZ.  And they are persistant until you change them.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, you got a permanent 3 song twist going.  Now, here's where the bard being on top of his/her game comes in.  <br>
<br>
Song 1, Song 2, and Song 3 are going.  Want to go pull with RoT?  Click RoT and that drops song 3.  However, you can click whatever song 3 was and in a few seconds move it back to song 1.   Needless to say, stuff like clickies, selo's pants, etc, are not counted.  RoT, charm, etc, ARE counted.  If it's a song, its counted against the 3.  If its off an item, it is not.  Same on AA.<br>
<br>
Can the servers handle this, beats me.  Maybe not.  But it's late, I'm bored, and I think I screwed up my power pool on my energy/energy blaster at level 18 so.../shrug.  WTB Stamina and SO enhancements...paying...err, ok?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45732" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:century gothic;font-size:medium;">Felmid Skyesong</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
